/* Conversions can be implicit or explicit. 

Implicit conversions = Happen automatically
Explicit conversions = Requires a 'Cast'. 

Example for implicit (converting 'int' to 'long'),
Example for explicit cast (converting 'int' to 'short') */


int x = 12345;       // int is a 32-bit integer
long y = x;          // Implicit converstion to 64-bit
short z = (short)x;  // Explicit conversion to 16-bit integer


